  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Disease Prevention and Surveillance at Points of Entry and Points of Control in the Democratic Republic of the Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project contributes to the interruption of disease transmission by reinforcing Ebola virus disease surveillance and prevention activities at points of entry (PoE) and points of control (PoC) through improved management of PoE/PoC operations. It is estimated that this project will support a total of 90 PoE/PoC (80 existing PoE/PoC and 10 new ones). The proposed project will prioritize strengthening disease surveillance and prevention at PoE/PoC that are epidemiologically critical, using available data pertaining to transmission trends, mobility routes, and population flows associated with the current Ebola virus epidemic in the Democratic Repulic of Congo.</narrative>
  </description>
